the new technology of current designs.","This fondue set is constructed of handcrafted copper 1.2 to 2 mm thick. It has a copper tin interior, polished copper exterior, and bronze handles fixed by copper rivets. The polished copper makes this a beautiful and classy-looking fondue pot. It comes with six color-coded fondue forks to lessen confusion during fondue parties. Guests are able to keep track of which fork belongs to them.","Copper heats faster and more evenly than other metals, so your fondue won&#39;t take a long time to melt. You can use it in the oven, as well as on gas, electric and halogen stovetops. If you have an induction stovetop, you can purchase Mauviel&#39;s induction stovetop interface disc separately.","It is recommended that you always cook over low to medium heat with this fondue pot. This limits the types of fondue you can make with it. Since most meats require high heat, it is not a good idea to try to serve meats in this fondue pot.","One problem with this fondue set is the chance of the color of the pot changing. While the copper color is beautiful and stylish, copper can change color over time with a lot of use. However, the copper&#39;s conductivity will not be affected.","The interior does not have a nonstick service, so cleaning this pot may not be an easy task. If food sticks to the inside of the pot, you can simply soak it in hot, soapy water. You cannot wash this pot in the dishwasher, though, which would be quicker and easier. Using bleach to clean the pan can damage it beyond repair. If your pot is damaged from normal wear and tear, though, you can restore its gleaming copper surface with Copperbrill cleaner.","You are limited in the types of food you can cook with this set. Due to its construction, you cannot make meats with this pot. It does make perfect cheese and chocolate dips, though, which tend to be the main fondue attractions. The copper it is made of looks beautiful and has excellent heat distribution, though the color and shine dims over time."]},"id":"8e252232-4768-40b2-a64e-78a38d5c2d6c","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_61617","url":"/mauviel-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"top-ten-reviews-staff","url":"/author/top-ten-reviews-staff","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","name":"Top Ten Reviews Staff","dateModified":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","id":"EcXXb3s8QKwvex3rQshgX5","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2014-12-16T17:18:41Z","datePublished":"2014-12-16T17:18:41Z","name":"Mauviel M'tradition Copper Fondue Set","synopsis":"The Mauviel M'tradition Copper Fondue Set is a unique fondue pot. Its features are that of a traditional fondue set, but it blends tradition with the new technology of current designs.","review":{"pros":[""],"cons":[""]},"strapline":"The Mauviel M'tradition Copper Fondue Set is a unique fondue pot. Its features are that of a traditional fondue set, but it blends tradition with the new technology of current designs.","language":"en","dateModified":"2014-12-16T17:18:41Z","id":"HmRcsyqhtwLQdB33pZdW78","meta":{"title":"Mauviel M'tradition Copper Fondue Set Review - Pros, Cons and Verdict","description":"The Mauviel M&#039;tradition Copper Fondue Set has a gorgeous exterior of polished copper that adds to the ambiance of a fondue party. Read about it here."},"products":[{"slug":"mauviel-mtradition-copper-fondue-set","url":"/product/mauviel-mtradition-copper-fondue-set","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T19:04:05Z","name":"Mauviel M'tradition Copper Fondue Set","dateModified":"2019-04-16T19:04:05Z","id":"pJNvmpSr78ACSxpmyoaD2A","dateImported":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","site":"toptenreviews"}],"dateImported":"2019-04-16T19:04:06Z","type":"review","template":"review","social":{"twitter":{"image":{"status":"","height":0,"path":"/vy2VBTn3MQybTYR8hNswWm.jpg","checksum":"","copyright":"","fileSize":0,"width":0,"caption":"","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T19:04:05Z","mimeType":"","name":"61589-m